main event: A UFO sighting was reported in Shreveport, Louisiana between 1954-1956, involving ground-radar observation without any photographs to support the claim.
interesting points: The reported sighting involved objects photographed during the period of 1955-1956, but the lack of supporting information and poor quality of the photographs made evaluation difficult.
The objects in the photographs were analyzed to be birds in the air, possibly waterfowl, with limited visibility due to cloudy sky conditions.
There was uncertainty and difficulty in properly evaluating the sighting due to the long time interval since the sighting and the lack of supporting information.
Enlargements of the objects in the photographs suggested that they appeared to be lights on the water, possibly presents, adding to the mystery of the sighting.
The report also highlighted the interesting results from technical returns, indicating the complexity of analyzing the reported UFO sighting.
